Could be coincidental - the front shift rod bushing
(in front of where the shift lever enters the rod) is
my guess unless the lever has been loosened at the
floorboard - 2 bolts - one ahead and one behind. If
the coupler came loose, you'd be unable to shift any
gears. -BaH

